        "responses": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=my data: {{ $json.output }}\n\n\n\nYou are an expert in financial data entry.\n\nYour input data will be a JSON object or text file containing optical character recognition (OCR) data from an invoice. It may contain missing fields, extra fields, or inconsistent formatting.\n\nYour task is:\n\n1. Extract data from the input into a strictly valid JSON object using the following example schema:\n\n{\n\"transaction\": {\n\"operation_id\": \"\",\n\"date\": \"\",\n\"time\": \"\",\n\"amount\": ,\n\"currency\": \"\",\n\"reason\": \"\",\n\"platform\": \"\"\n},\n\"sender\": {\n\"name\": \"\",\n\"tax_ID\": \"\",\n\"entity\": \"\"\n},\n\"receiver\": {\n\"name\": \"\",\n\"tax_ID\": \"\",\n\"entity\": \"\"\n\n}\n}\n\n2. Remove any fields not listed above.\n\n3. If a value is missing or ambiguous, set it to null.\n\n4. Format \"LineItems\" as a dictionary list with the specified keys and ensure all line item fields are present.\n\n5. Generate only the sanitized, strictly valid, Airtable-ready JSON object. Do not include any additional explanation or text.\n\nRegarding numeric fields (\"TotalAmount\" and all numeric fields in \"LineItems\"):\n\n1. All numeric fields must be formatted as valid JSON numbers (e.g., 17000, 1210.50) or set to null.\n\n2. You MUST remove all currency symbols (e.g., \"$\", \"€\").\n\n3. You MUST remove all thousands separators (e.g., \",\").\n\n4. Ensure that any decimal separator is a period \".\" (for example, convert \"12.50\" to 12.50).\n\n5. For example: convert \"€17000\" to 17000. Convert \"1210.50\" to 1210.50.\n\nCritical: Fields MUST be populated ONLY with the input data.\n\nInput:\n\n[Run previous nodes for preview] {{ $json.output }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {
          "textFormat": {
            "textOptions": {
